text:
The 2005 Bolivian general elections were held early on December 18, 2005. The ballot was originally scheduled for 2007. The two main candidates for the presidency were Evo Morales, of the Movement towards Socialism, and Jorge Quiroga Ramírez, leader of the Democratic and Social Power (PODEMOS) and ex-leader of Nationalist Democratic Action (ADN; Acción Democrática Nacionalista).
